{
  "texts": [
    "A rare exception is the memory-related interactions between non-human agents, which take place not in the backend but via the interfaces used by human agents.",
    "One particular example is Wikipedia, where non-human agents (i.e.",
    "Wikipedia bots) interact with each other while working on the articles, including the ones dealing with the collective and individual past.",
    "At times, these agents conflict by reverting changes made by other robotic agents (Tsvetkova et al. 2017).",
    "Due to such robot-to-robot communication occurring in the same environment as the one used by humans and in a format comprehensible for humans (i.e."
  ]
}